review_translated_text: Very pleasant experience at Cafe Marhaba located in the Fetal city in the wilaya of Blida. A cafe in the purest Algerian tradition, with homemade oriental pastries and Western pastries and pastries that have nothing to envy to Parisian bakeries. Without forgetting the excellent hard-boiled eggs of the day and the apricot jam butter baguettes which recall the atmosphere of Parisian bistros in the 1960s. If you want to drink orangina from the ancestral factory, that of blida, a strawberry milk, mint tea, cream or strong coffee, you've come to the right place. In addition, Fatah the manager, who speaks perfect French, will provide entertainment. Tariff issue. The prices are very low despite the quality of the products.
